HEADWORD: Cliff
<hw>Cliff</hw> <pr>(kl⟦icr⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>clif</ets>, <ets>cloef</ets>; akin to OS. <ets>klif</ets>, D.
<ets>klif</ets>, <ets>klip</ets>, Icel. <ets>klif</ets>, Dan. & G.
<ets>klippe</ets>, Sw. <ets>klippa</ets>; perh. orig. <ets>a climbing
place</ets>. See <er>Climb</er>.]</ety> <def>A high, steep rock; a
precipice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cliff swallow</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a North
American swallow (<spn>Petrochelidon lunifrons</spn>), which builds its
nest against cliffs; the <altname>eaves swallow</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

